column1: Study: Temperature-Induced Shifts in Chemosensory Responses of Hermissenda crassicornis to Predator and Conspecific Cues
Course: BMSC Fall Program 2024, Directed Studies (MRSC 507, MRNE 400)
Members: Brianna Over, Fiona Parker and Luca Meyknecht

column2: Specimens were placed in a long container with a grid where they were allowed to react to chemical cues, they were recorded during this
trial time. Data from the trial period in nudi_treatmentdata and in nudi_vids. Footage was then analyed in Image J and recorded data
can be found in pred_trials, cons_trials and nudi_size.

column3: name of the file analyzed in ImageJ
"predator" for predatory cues, or "conspecific" for conspecific cues
whether they received the treatment as their first ("1") or second ("2") trial
image frame number analyzed in ImageJ (1-8 or 1-11 for conspecific and predatory respectively); "NA" was recorded for trials stopped early due to nudibranchs climbing on the water surface
x values not corrected for original position
y values not corrected for original position
average velocity of nudi per frame
degrees before being corrected for a 360° circle instead of a +/- 180° quadrant
the change in ° from the previous track position
x values corrected for original position
y values corrected for original position
degrees corrected for a 360° circle instead of a +/- 180° quadrant
